   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, Samuel Andrew Baker in South Carrolton, Ky. to Joseph Warren Baker in Whitley County, Ind.</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Samuel Andrew Baker wrote to his father, Joseph Warren Baker, on January 28, 1862. He mentioned having a boil on his forehead. He mentioned he had been looking for a letter from home for some time. He mentioned his Colonel was sick and on furlough and that they had another leader. He was a little homesick. He had not received any pay for a long time and didn&apos;t really expect to get any. He didn&apos;t have money for postage so had had not written home much. His company was expecting an attack from the rebels and had prepared for that. He mentioned a funny story about a raccoon scaring the troops. He mentioned the company was fired upon while on piquet guard.</abstract>
